BLACKROC Software Engineering are excited to bring this extraordinary
opportunity to the Brisbane market.  
  
Working alongside a distributed cross-functional team, you'll be responsible
for the ongoing development and improvement of a global technology platform.
As part of this team, you'll help shape technology strategy and policy,
influence engineering culture and conduct R&D to ensure scalability and
reliability of the platform.  
  
As part of your responsibilities, you’ll be creating applications tailored to
the needs of specific service sectors. Drive real value for clients on their
advanced global platform using the latest .NET and React, supported by a
microservice infrastructure on AWS. As a Senior Engineer you will lead
technology decisions, set standards, mentor team members, and deliver a
robust, scalable, and maintainable solution.  
Core Tech Stack:  

  * .NET 6+ 
  * Typescript 4+ 
  * React 18+ 
  * SQL Server 
  * Mongo DB 
  * Kubernetes 
  * AWS. 
  * Azure DevOps for CI/CD 
Key Tasks and Requirements:  

  * Design, develop, test, deploy, maintain, and improve software. 
  * Manage project priorities, deadlines, and deliverables. 
  * Ownership of all aspects of their software product: architecture, quality & user experience. 
  * Perform regular code reviews, mentor, and guide the team to improve coding practices. 
  * Be a team enabler. 
About you:  

  * Enthusiastic and motivated developer with a track record of diverse project experience in agile environments, dedicated to producing high-quality work while aligning with business objectives. 
  * Proficient in object-oriented principles, SOLID, and design patterns, prioritizing code efficiency, legibility, testability, and maintainability. 
  * Extensive experience aligning with the majority of our tech stack. 
  * Valued knowledge or involvement in the legal and conveyancing industry. 
  
Offering a generous renumeration package and lovely new state of the art
offices in the CBD!  
  
